            <bug_when>2008-03-07 20:11:44 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The table cell editor is currently being focus using a &quot;one&quot; timer firing after 0ms. This works as long as the editor is not being removed before the timer goes off. This sometimes happened accidentally when clicking &quot;wildly&quot; into the table. And for 100% the editor is gone when listening to &quot;cellDblClicked&quot; events on Table or Scroller and invoking scroller.cancelEditing().

So I suppose to use the &quot;appear&quot; event instead plus a non-anonymous event handler being removed in the cancelEditing-method.

See qx.ui.table.pane.Scroller#startEditing (line 1663ff).</thetext>
          </long_desc>
